## 9. Summary (For Thesis Writing)

> TERTIAN (An et al., 2022) introduces a time-aware transformer combined with hierarchical attention to model irregular and heterogeneous clinical time-series data. By explicitly incorporating time intervals and multi-level feature interactions, it significantly improves prediction performance over standard models. This architecture serves as the primary foundation for the proposed Temporal Attention Network (TAN), which adapts these concepts to high-frequency intraoperative data for cardiac arrest prediction.

